==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: rubella
<hw>ru*bel"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. L.
<ets>rubellus</ets> reddish.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An acute but
mild viral infection characterized by a dusky red cutaneous eruption
resembling that of measles, but attended by only mild respiratory
problems or fever; -- called also <altname>German measles</altname>. The
infective virus is called <causedby>Rubella virus</causedby>, or
<gen>Rubivirus</gen>. If contracted by a woman during the first several
months of pregnancy, <ex>rubella</ex> may cause serious abnormalities in
the fetus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>rubella virus</ent>⟦br⟧
